A man in his 30s was hit by a car after he was ejected through the windscreen of his rolling car on the R617 towards Kokstad in the KwaZulu-Natal Midlands on Sunday. According to Underberg Emergency Medical Services, the man lost control of his car and it rolled multiple times. He was ejected from the car and unfortunately another car came around the bend and hit him. He died at the scene. Five people, including a two-year-old girl were injured. Meanwhile, two people died in a crash involving three cars in Phoenix outside Durban on Saturday afternoon. Spokesperson for Reaction Unit South Africa, Prem Balram, said a Nissan Sentra driving in the direction of the Phoenix Highway veered into oncoming traffic before it knocked into the side of a Toyota Quantum before colliding head on into a VW Polo. “The driver of the Nissan Sentra died later at the hospital while and a woman who was seated at the rear of the VW Polo and her six-year-old daughter were injured,” said Balram.